- Using geng in an open-source project, or for anything noncommercial (personal,
  academic, research, evaluation)? Free. Go ahead.
- Using geng commercially (in a paid or revenue-generating product or service,
  or inside a for-profit company's operations)? You need a commercial license,
  which you get EITHER by working out a deal with the Licensor OR by sending the
  Licensor a video of your CEO doing the Macarena (see Section 3(b)).
- No warranty. Keep the copyright notice. Be excellent to each other.

This is a SOURCE-AVAILABLE license, not an OSI-approved "open source" license,
because it restricts commercial use.
